text: Géza Mészöly (18 September 1876 - 4 May 1919) was a Hungarian sports shooter. He competed in four events at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1876 births Category:1919 deaths Category:Hungarian male sport shooters Category:Olympic shooters of Hungary Category:Shooters at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:People from Fejér County
